data.name: UDPDiscoveryButton.ToolTip
data.value:
When enabled, TunerViewer will use a UDP broadcast to discover devices on the local subnet. This method is enabled by default.
When disabled, TunerViewer will parse the ARP table looking for known MAC addresses and their assocaited IP addressses. This method is inferior, and disabled by default. (This is the method used for remote discovery)

data.name: UseHDHRConfigButton.ToolTip
data.value:
Enabling "Use HDHRConfig" will force TunerViewer to use HDHomerun_config.exe when updating tuner info. This has the potential to reduce loads on the device.
Requires the HDHomerun_config.exe executable to be located in the default installation path:
"c:\Program Files\SiliconDust\HDHomerun\..."
This feature is disabled by default, and TunerViewer will parse this information from HTML downloaded from the device.

data.name: HDHRDiscoverButton.ToolTip
data.value:
When enabled, TunerViewer will execute hdhomerun_config "discover" on the remote host when discovering remote devices. This allows for the same results as using the UDP discovery protocol. This requires the existence of the hdhomerun_config.exe in the default path.
When disabled, TunerViewer will execute an ARP command on the remote host, and parse its output looking for known MAC addresses.
